events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Amari Cooper caught two of AJ McCarron's four touchdown passes Saturday as No. 1 Alabama defeated Tennessee 44-13 for its sixth consecutive victory over the Volunteers.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCarron, Cooper lead way as Bama rips Vols

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Jeff Driskel threw four touchdown passes -- three of them after turnovers -- and No. 3 Florida matched its win total from last season with a 44-11 drubbing of ninth-ranked South Carolina on Saturday.

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Collin Klein ran for four touchdowns and threw three TD passes as No. 4 Kansas State got little resistance from No. 17 West Virginia in a 55-14 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klein, Kansas State roll Smith, WVU

events.name: BYU Cougars at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Theo Riddick ran for a career-high 143 yards, Cierre Wood added 114 yards as No. 5 Notre Dame rallied for a 17-14 victory on Saturday.

events.name: LSU Tigers at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Jeremy Hill rushed for a career-high 127 yards and a touchdown, and No. 6 LSU rallied from an early deficit to beat Texas A&M (No. 18 BCS, No. 20 AP) 24-19 at Kyle Field on Saturday.

events.name: Utah Utes at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: Oregon State's defense helped out when quarterback Cody Vaz struggled in the rain, and the No. 8 Beavers remained undefeated with a 21-7 victory over Utah on Saturday night that gave them their best start in more than a century.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oregon State stays perfect with win over Utah

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Landry Jones threw for 291 yards and three touchdowns, and Oklahoma scored on a kickoff return and a punt return in the same game for the first time in school history while clobbering Kansas 52-7 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 9 Sooners clobber Jayhawks behind Jones

events.name: Colorado Buffaloes at USC Trojans

headlines.description: USC beat Colorado 50-6 on Saturday.

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Aaron Murray threw four touchdown passes to become the school's career leader, with the first three crucial in rallying the No. 13 Bulldogs for a 29-24 victory over Kentucky.

events.name: Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Tyler Russell threw for 191 yards and three touchdowns, Johnthan Banks tied a school record with his 16th career interception and No. 15 Mississippi State pulled away in the second half to beat Middle Tennessee 45-3 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Russell throws 3 TDs, helps Miss. St. pull away

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: EJ Manuel threw for 229 yards, Devonta Freeman ran for a pair of fourth-quarter touchdowns and No. 12 Florida State overcame a shaky start to beat Miami 33-20 on Saturday night, the Seminoles' third straight win over their archrival.

events.name: Rutgers Scarlet Knights at Temple Owls

headlines.description: Gary Nova threw four touchdown passes in the second half to lead Rutgers (No. 15 BCS, No. 19 AP) to a 35-10 comeback victory over Temple on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nova (4 TDs) fuels Rutgers' rally vs. Temple

events.name: South Florida Bulls at Louisville Cardinals

headlines.description: Teddy Bridgewater threw an 11-yard touchdown pass to Eli Rogers with 1:35 left, and the 16th-ranked Cardinals edged South Florida 27-25 on Saturday for their best beginning to season since 2006.

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Seth Doege threw seven touchdowns, three in overtime, and No. 18 Texas Tech won 56-53 at TCU after blowing a late 10-point lead Saturday.

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd ran for two touchdowns and passed for another and Jonathan Meeks had a 74-yard interception return for score as No. 14 Clemson won its third straight over Virginia Tech, 38-17, on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Meeks, No. 19 Clemson pick off VT

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Stepfan Taylor ran for a career-high 189 yards and one touchdown, and Stanford overwhelmed rival California 21-3 on Saturday for its third straight Big Game victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford rips Cal, wins 3rd Big Game in row

events.name: Cincinnati Bearcats at Toledo Rockets

headlines.description: Toledo's Bernard Reedy scored on a 91-yard kickoff return to lead the Rockets over No. 21 Cincinnati 29-23 Saturday night, handing the Bearcats their first loss of the season.

events.name: UNLV Rebels at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: D.J. Harper rushed for two touchdowns and Boise State's defense had one as well to help the Broncos (No. 22 BCS, No. 24 AP) rout UNLV 32-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boise St.'s dominating D limits UNLV during rout

events.name: Iowa State Cyclones at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: J.W. Walsh threw for 415 yards and a touchdown, and Joseph Randle scored twice and set up another touchdown with a big fourth-quarter run as Oklahoma State beat Iowa State (No. 24 BCS) 31-10 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Walsh, Oklahoma State upend No. 24 Iowa St.

events.name: Baylor Bears at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Joe Bergeron ran for five touchdowns and Texas outlasted Baylor 56-50 Saturday night in another wild one in the Big 12, snapping the Longhorns' two-game losing skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bergeron's five TDs help Texas outlast Baylor

events.name: Bowling Green Falcons at UMass Minutemen

headlines.description: Bowling Green 24, UMass 0

events.name: Purdue Boilermakers at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Kenny Guiton came off the bench in relief of quarterback Braxton Miller to lead touchdown drives in the final minute of regulation and in overtime, with Carlos Hyde scoring on a 1-yard run to clinch Ohio State's 29-22 victory over Purdue on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ohio State loses QB Miller, edges Purdue in OT

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: James White raced 15 times through Minnesota's defense for 175 yards rushing and three touchdowns, carrying Wisconsin to a 38-13 victory over Minnesota on Saturday, the ninth straight time the Badgers have beaten the Gophers to keep Paul Bunyan's Axe.
headlines.shortLinkText: White, Ball power Badgers' rout of Gophers

events.name: Northern Illinois Huskies at Akron Zips

headlines.description: N. Illinois 37, Akron 7

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Vanderbilt Commodores

headlines.description: Zac Stacy ran for 169 yards and a touchdown and Vanderbilt beat Auburn 17-13 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vandy sends Auburn to worst start since '52

events.name: Wake Forest Demon Deacons at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: Chad Hedlund kicked three field goals, and Wake Forest returned from an open week with a much-improved defense and beat mistake-prone Virginia 16-10 on Saturday, the Cavaliers' sixth consecutive loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hedlund's three FGs help Wake past Virginia

headlines.description: E. Michigan 48, Army 38

Boston College Eagles at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Tevin Washington ran for two touchdowns and backup quarterback Vad Lee also accounted for two scores, leading Georgia Tech to a 37-17 victory over Boston College in a matchup of struggling Atlantic Coast Conference teams Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia Tech tops Boston College, snaps skid

events.name: New Mexico State Aggies at Utah State Aggies

headlines.description: Utah St. 41, New Mexico St. 7

events.name: Florida Atlantic Owls at South Alabama Jaguars
Nebraska Cornhuskers at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Taylor Martinez threw for 342 yards and three touchdowns and Nebraska rallied to beat Northwestern 29-28 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nebraska rallies, clips Northwestern on late TD

events.name: NC State Wolfpack at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Mike Glennon directed a frantic drive to set up a 43-yard field goal by Niklas Sade with 32 seconds left, and North Carolina State overcame a valiant performance by Maryland backup quarterback Devin Burns in a 20-18 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: NC State survives as Maryland misses late FG

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Brendan Gibbons made a 38-yard field goal with 5 seconds left, lifting Michigan (No. 23 AP) to a 12-10 win over Michigan State on Saturday.

headlines.description: Tulsa 28, Rice 24

headlines.description: Richmond 35, James Madison 29

headlines.description: Wofford 38, Appalachian St. 28

events.name: Pittsburgh Panthers at Buffalo Bulls

headlines.description: Ray Graham and Rushel Shell each scored a touchdown rushing to help the Pittsburgh Panthers snap a two-game skid with a 20-6 win over the Buffalo Bulls on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pittsburgh beats Buffalo, snaps two-game skid

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Navy Midshipmen

headlines.description: Keenan Reynolds completed a 4-yard touchdown pass to Matt Aiken with 2:02 to play and Nick Sloan added the point after as Navy rallied for a 31-30 win over Indiana on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Navy rallies for first win vs. Big Ten since '79

North Carolina Tar Heels at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: Sean Renfree's 5-yard touchdown pass to Jamison Crowder on fourth down with 13 seconds left lifted Duke past North Carolina 33-30 on Saturday night and made the Blue Devils bowl eligible for the first time since 1994.
headlines.shortLinkText: Duke now bowl eligible for 1st time since 1994

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: Bill Belton ran for 103 yards and three touchdowns and surging Penn State throttled Iowa 38-14 on Saturday night for its fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn State rocks Iowa for 5th straight victory

events.name: Washington Huskies at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Matt Scott threw for 256 yards and four touchdowns, Ka'Deem Carey ran for 172 yards and Arizona raced out of its bye week with a 52-17 rout over Washington Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arizona rolls past Washington following bye
